    {
        "url": "/quotes/fernando_botero_756579",
        "quote": "My popularity has to do with the divorce between modern art, where everything is obscure, and the viewer who often feels he needs a professor to tell them whether it's good or not. I believe a painting has to talk directly to the viewer, with composition, color and design, without a professor to explain it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Fernando Botero",
            "url": "/quotes/fernando_botero_756579"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
